@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Project";
}

<section class="surface-card info-card">
    <h2 class="section-title mb-3">About SalesLedger</h2>
    <p>SalesLedger is a portfolio-oriented ASP.NET Core MVC application for operational sales and transaction management. It was designed to look credible for employers while also serving as a realistic stepping stone toward a Data Warehouse or Business Intelligence thesis project.</p>

    <div class="row g-4 mt-1">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3 class="section-title">Architecture Focus</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Domain entities are separated from infrastructure and UI concerns.</li>
                <li>EF Core with SQL Server powers the operational data model and seed data.</li>
                <li>Services handle business logic and keep controllers lightweight.</li>
                <li>View models shape pages and forms without exposing persistence objects directly.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3 class="section-title">Data Warehouse Direction</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>FactSales:</strong> transaction amount, quantity, payment, source and keys.</li>
                <li><strong>DimSeller:</strong> seller name, company and contact attributes.</li>
                <li><strong>DimProduct:</strong> reusable product master data and category classification.</li>
                <li><strong>DimCustomer:</strong> lightweight buyer information when available.</li>
                <li><strong>DimDate:</strong> transaction dates ready for monthly and yearly analysis.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
